@node install "How to install MoreText?"

Installation of MoreText is very simple.

Just copy MoreText executable to some directory in your path,
and copy MoreText.guide to HELP:English directory so
you can use online help.

@endnode

@node usage "How to use MoreText?"
Some information concerning the usage of MoreText.

NOTE: MoreText requires Kickstart 2.0 (V36) or greater to work.


                  @{" Command line arguments " link cmdline}

                  @{" Keyboard commands      " link keycmds}


@endnode

@node cmdline "Command line parameters"

MoreText has following command line template:

FILE/A,LINES/N,COLUMNS/N,ALTCOLOR/S,STARTNODE/K,NOFILELINKS/S,QUERYCON/S,
ALTCURSOR/S

         FILE        : Name of the file to view.
                       This is the only parameter required to get MoreText
                       running.

         LINES       : Number of lines to use. (Default is 24)

         COLUMNS     : Number of columns to use. (Default is 80)

         ALTCOLOR    : With this option on, MoreText uses different ANSI
                       codes which makes it more suitable for CLI usage.

         STARTNODE   : With this argument you can specify starting
                       AmigaGuide node, which will be used instead
                       of "main" node. Home (7) key will also jump to
                       this node.

         NOFILELINKS : This option is for SysOps that do not want BBS users
                       to use AmigaGuide links to view other files or guides
                       and thus possibly violate the protection system
                       provided by BBS software.

         QUERYCON    : When this option is on, every time display
                       is redrawn MoreText queries console handler
                       for number of lines and columns to use.
                       Not all console handlers support querying.

                       If LINES and/or COLUMNS arguments are specified,
                       QUERYCON option is ignored.

         ALTCURSOR   : When this option is on, cursor keys have different
                       actions when viewing AmigaGuides:

                       CURSOR DOWN and CURSOR RIGHT = Find next link
                       CURSOR UP   and CURSOR LEFT  = Find previous link

@endnode

@node keycmds "Keyboard commands"
Description of MoreText's keyboard commands.
Press Q to quit reading help.

CURSOR UP, 8         SCROLL ONE LINE UP

CURSOR DOWN, 2       SCROLL ONE LINE DOWN

9, BACKSPACE         JUMP ONE PAGE UP

3, SPACE             JUMP ONE PAGE DOWN

CURSOR LEFT, 4       SCROLL ONE PAGE UP

CURSOR RIGHT, 6      SCROLL ONE PAGE DOWN

7                    GO TO THE START OF TEXT

                     Goes to the first line of text or to main node 
                     if you are viewing AmigaGuides.

1                    GO TO THE END OF TEXT

s , /                SEARCH FOR A STRING IN TEXT

                     You will be prompted for a string to search.
                     The search is always case-insensitive and
                     starts from the line after current line.

n                    SEARCH FOR NEXT OCCURRENCE

                     This is exactly same as previous command,
                     except that it uses previosly given
                     search string.

j                    JUMP TO LINE

                     You will be prompted for a line number to jump to.

- , u                RETRACE

                     With this key, you can "undo" your searches, line
                     jumps and link jumps. You will return to a position
                     you were before (including links to other files).

                     Currently you can "undo" up to 32 jumps in one file,
                     and unlimited jumps to other files.

r                    REDRAW SCREEN

                     If for some reason, the display is messed up
                     you can issue full redraw with this key.

q                    QUIT CURRENT

                     Quit reading current document. If this was
                     the last document, MoreText quits completely.

Q                    QUIT ALL

                     Quits MoreText completely, regardless of
                     how many documents you have in memory.

h                    DISPLAY SHORT LIST OF COMMANDS

H                    DISPLAY THIS HELP TEXT

AmigaGuide control keys. These keys are only usable when viewing AmigaGuides.

a                    TOGGLE BETWEEN NORMAL / AMIGAGUIDE MODE

                     If for some reason you want AmigaGuide to be
                     displayed as normal text, use this key.
                     Returning back to the AmigaGuide mode is also
                     achieved with the same key.

TAB                  FIND NEXT LINK

                     Scan for next link in current node. If link
                     is found it will be highlighted.

p                    FIND PREVIOUS LINK

                     Same as TAB key, except that the search will commence
                     backwards.

RETURN               USE CURRENT LINK

                     With this key you can jump to the location pointed
                     by highlighted link.

i                    JUMP TO INDEX NODE

                     If index node is available in the guide you are
                     reading, the program will jump there.
                     Naturally jump to index node can be retraced.

@endnode

